# Application Settings
PROJECT_NAME=C2 Framework
DEBUG=True
API_V1_STR=/api/v1

# Database Settings
POSTGRES_SERVER=localhost
POSTGRES_USER=c2user
POSTGRES_PASSWORD=c2password
POSTGRES_DB=c2db
POSTGRES_PORT=5432

# Security
SECRET_KEY=your-super-secret-key-change-this-in-production-min-32-characters
ALGORITHM=HS256
ACCESS_TOKEN_EXPIRE_MINUTES=30

# Encryption (we'll generate this properly later)
ENCRYPTION_KEY=WaKvybHPpabwSE8nvhNmgbb6kcP8zh08GMzXnw43U1U=

# CORS (Frontend URL)
BACKEND_CORS_ORIGINS=["http://localhost:3000","http://localhost:5173"]

# First Admin User
FIRST_SUPERUSER_EMAIL=admin@c2framework.com
FIRST_SUPERUSER_PASSWORD=changethis123
```

#**What each setting means:**
```
#PROJECT_NAME = What appears in API docs
#DEBUG = Shows detailed errors (True for development)
#API_V1_STR = Prefix for all API routes

#POSTGRES_* = Database connection info
#  - SERVER = Where database is running
#  - USER = Database username
#  - PASSWORD = Database password
#  - DB = Database name
#  - PORT = Database port (5432 is default)

#SECRET_KEY = Used to sign JWT tokens (MUST be secret!)
#ALGORITHM = Encryption algorithm for JWT
#ACCESS_TOKEN_EXPIRE_MINUTES = How long tokens last

#ENCRYPTION_KEY = For encrypting agent communications
#BACKEND_CORS_ORIGINS = Which websites can access API
#FIRST_SUPERUSER_* = Initial admin account 